                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="menarinimaster/components/text"
                            text="&lt;p>Today the Menarini Eco-Team was created.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>The team is made up of seven employees from various company sectors, the majority female, and stems from the wide-spread sensibility of its employees towards active environmental sustainability.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;em>&amp;ldquo;The company follows the highest standards of environmental protection according to the ISO 14001 certification,&amp;rdquo; commented Angela, Eco-Team Coordinator. &amp;ldquo;This provided the base and motivated us to make our own contribution to the cause by identifying daily improvements involving material and energetic resources.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>On the agenda is increased differentiated waste disposal and the introduction of new materials that are recycled or provided by certified suppliers.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>&amp;ldquo;Our initial target areas concern non-carbon copy paper and plastic cups.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>Menarini is proud to strengthen its commitment to the environment and has created the slogan, &amp;ldquo;Eco-Team: We All Belong.&amp;rdquo; &lt;/p>"
